{
  "stem": "6719.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And uh, so when she was found-- my wife-- they tried to get those two together-- you know, Henry, who became a United States interpreter-- English, and French, and Flemish, and German-- and my wife, who lived in Salzburg.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when we got married, and she brought all her things over to where I lived-- we were married-- she brought some correspondence over.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I saw a letter down there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It said Henry Harman, US interpreter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said-- funny enough, I said to her, I said, you know, I said, Henry Hartman, I knew a Heinrich Hartman, see.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I knew he was an interpreter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, tell me-- just by that-- I said, has he got a--a-- a--a-- a leg that's stiff?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She says, yeah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said, my god, you could've, should've married this?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She said, you know, I met him, but I didn't like him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I said, that was it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "These are the amus-- there are some amusing stories that are behind there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "What, what, what's your wife's name?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Claire.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "C-L-A-I-R-E.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kimerling, K-I-M-E-R-L-I-N-G.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was a submarine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was hidden in Austria.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Uh, she was sent to a labor camp in, uh, Germany, I think in 19 hundred and-- what was it? 40? 40, I think.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a labor camp that-- I mean, they worked in a factory, in a leather factory.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And uh, then they were sent back by train to Vienna, and she was supposed to report to the school-- and uh, to a school that was converted into the same place like Mechelen, where we were.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And somehow, thanks god-- I used that for the second time already.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For a non-believer, that's not bad-- she uh-- she had a hunch.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
